<br>
Who am I? I am a ranger that got caught in the hybrid pinch just like you did. That was somewhat offended by &quot;rangers suck&quot; post and the general bashing on the class made by people that don't play rangers. <br>
<br>
When Plainswalker made his post I was fairly disappointed that one of our more respected rangers made a post like that.  I thought that post was bad and I think this one smacks alot of the same irritating things as his did. Although you may not be respected by all on this server due to what you just pointed out by disgruntled feelings you are still one of the more prolilific paladins on our server. This post may have been meant as a &quot;Gah!! I need some help figuring out what to do to better serve my groups&quot; but I can tell you this, people will read this and start to think hey yeah pallies do suck I don't need them in my group just like what happened to the rangers awhile back.<br>
<br>
Since you just got mad at the first couple of sentences in my first post, I'll try this again....<br>
<br>
You got caught in the hybrid pinch. What you need to do is grab some friends and go somewhere for exp and try some different weapon and spell combos. You don't have an agro problem like the rangers did. You need to basically create that agro. I will admit that I don't know the paladin class well  but it seems you are having a hard time with doing enough damage to be viable to your groups. All I can say is there must be a weapon and spell combo for paladins to do greater damage just like there was a combo for rangers to do damage and survive without being a mana drain to the clerics.<br>
<br>
Now if I had offened you with the other post I apologize for that. That wasn't the intent of the post. <br>
<br>
The only worthless/useless classes are those that are played by people who don't know what they are doing. Like it or not the hybrids have to change their roles at some point but are still viable group classes<br>
<br>
<br>
