<br>
<br>
but at least I'm starting to feel comfortable with myself again. My base ac is very high thanks to my sword, and when I finally get around to finishing some Skyshrine armor quests, I'll have very nice stats and ac. <br>
<br>
Some people say stats are useless, but I have to semi-disagree. WIS is very important to me. Anyone who has grouped with me before knows that if I'm in the group, evac is rarely ever called. I have on countless times used my massive mana pool to keep the party together long after the cleric has gone oom, and where if a warrior, ranger, or sk was in my place, the group would have died or had to evac.<br>
<br>
I may not have the highest ac that other paladins do, I may not even have the same ac as some uber rangers do, but what I do have that separates me from the rest is the ability to play the paladin class full tilt and make it look GOOD.<br>
<br>
I'm a hybrid. <br>
